               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350302-name-934" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-934" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-934" type="surname" value="JACKSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-934" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY JACKSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I had the care of Esther Smith on the 17th of Fe<lb></lb>bruary—she is the daughter of Frederick Robert Smith, who lives in St. Pancras—I was out with the child, which is three months old—I saw the two prisoners, but did not see them take the child's necklace off, but it was taken off the child's neck—this is it—the prisoners were taken directly.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350302-name-935" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-935" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-935" type="surname" value="COLTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-935" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM COLTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a broker's shop, at Battle-bridge. On the 17th of February, I was sitting in my parlour, and saw this witness stand<lb></lb>ing at my shop looking at some pictures—the two prisoners stood one on each side of her—Barber took the necklace off the child's neck—they walked off—I pursued, and saw Barber—he threw this necklace at me, and while I picked that up, he made off, but he was taken afterwards.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350302-name-936" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-936" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-936" type="surname" value="CADBY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350302-name-936" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH CADBY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a constable, and was with Colton—I saw the two prisoners—I saw Rider put his hand to the child's neck, but Barber took off the necklace—we pursued them—I took Rider—Barber escaped then, but was taken on Sunday night.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Rider's Defence.</hi> I saw the necklace at her feet, and took it up—this man came after me—I threw the necklace at him.</p>
               <p>(The prisoners received a good character.)</p>
